\begin_layout Solution
So,
 let 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 be a real,
 and 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 a forcing condition.
 Then,
 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 has countable domain,
 so there are only countably many 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

columns
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $F\circ f\colon\omega_{1}\times\omega\to2$
\end_inset

 that 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 forces.
 Thus,
 we can just extend 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

